crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The code uses the Windows Scripting Host (WSH) to perform two actions. First, it creates a PowerShell script file named "pros.ps1" in the temporary directory. The path is constructed using environment variables. Then, it executes this PowerShell script using `powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass`, which disables the execution policy and allows the script to run.  Second, it uses the `schtasks` command to delete a scheduled task named "MicrosoftEdgeUpdateTaskMachineDDL". The `/F` switch forces the deletion without prompting.
